Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on
high heat. Add the @Basmati Rice{150%grams} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the #pan{}. Cover with
a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, halve the @Green Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds.
Chop into small chunks.

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{40%grams}.

Drain and rinse the @Mixed Beans{1%carton} in a sieve.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in another large saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced Chorizo{90%grams} and pepper chunks and cook,
stirring, for ~{3-4%mins}.

Add the @Cajun Spice Mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things
milder) and @Worcester Sauce{7.5%grams} to the pan. Cook for ~{30%secs}.

Stir in the @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%grams}, @Finely Chopped Tomatoes{1%carton},
@sugar{1/2%tsp} and mixed beans.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened,
~{5-6%mins}.

Meanwhile, pop the @Soured Cream{75%grams} into a small #bowl{}.

Add a pinch of salt and @pepper{}. Mix well.

Stir the @Baby Spinach{40%grams} into the stew a handful at a time until
wilted and piping hot, ~{2-3%mins}.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then share between your bowls.

Top with the chorizo and bean stew, a dollop of soured cream and sprinkle
over the cheese. Enjoy!